		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Xious wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I may also make some NESpander Light (TM) units that only add extra audio and the FC port</div><br />I can see demand for this, especially if you can manage to sell some compatible FC-to-NES adapters along with them.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">It's also catchy and easy to remember.</div>
<br />NES<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pandering_%28politics%29" class="postlink">pander</a> == NESsay-what-your-audience-wants-to-hear.
<br />
<br />But I will estimate that mapper sound is probably too big to fit on a practical CPLD. Even a single pulse wave takes at least 33 macrocells: 20 for the period divider, 5 for duty cycle processing, and 8 for PDM output.

		

